Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 172
Edition:
Quote: Even then they [oysters] are subject to an ingenious predator, the OysterBorer which, as his name implies, bores a hole into the helpless oyster's shell - and devours it.
